                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.00/1148</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-02-27T11:00:00-05:29">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 27, 1917—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Delayed radio from Guantanamo Naval Station just received says expected to land
                    two hundred men midnight Sunday in Guantanamo town, as systematic destruction
                    cane had commenced and disorder and danger to life threatened.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gonzales</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
